commit.message: [include/glbopts.h] Only define isinf on windows

[include/ecos.h] Update ECOS version number

The ECOS version number is manually incremented. This change increments
it to the next version.
[ecos_bb] Declare functions as static when possible
[ecos_bb] Rename INFINITY to ECOS_INFINITY

[include/glblopts.h] Make ECOS_INFINITY and ECOS_NAN standard

See, for instance, json-c
(https://github.com/json-c/json-c/blob/master/math_compat.h).

We also define the isinf macro if it isn't already defined (usually on
Windows or a pre-C99 compiler).

[include/ecos_bb.h] Remove (redefintion) of MSVC macros

Newer versions of MSVC have the INFINTY macro defined, so will throw
warnings that we've redefined them. Removing them.

[include/ecos_bb] Formatting and inline

This commit fixes some formatting issues with the branch and bound
header files. We also remove the inline compiler hints so that we don't
need to special case C89 compilers on Windows. Besides, a better
compiler will figure it out anyway (in theory).
Merge branch 'dbregman-master' into develop

[include/ctrlc.h] Remove OS-specific bits

The OS-specific bits in ctlrc.h are now in the source file src/ctrlc.c.
It's unclear whether this will break all sorts of things.... :)
[src/ctrlc.c] Formatting whitespace
